@startuml Rancher-to-Rancher Benchmarking
title **Use Case: Regional Benchmarking**\nTwo ranchers share grazing data to compare SOC outcomes

skinparam backgroundColor #FEFEFE
skinparam sequenceArrowThickness 2
skinparam sequenceParticipantBorderColor #424242
skinparam sequenceLifeLineBorderColor #9E9E9E
skinparam noteBackgroundColor #FFF9C4
skinparam noteBorderColor #F9A825
skinparam sequenceGroupBackgroundColor #E8F5E9
skinparam sequenceGroupBorderColor #2E7D32
skinparam sequenceDividerBackgroundColor #E3F2FD

actor "Sarah Chen\n(White Buffalo\nLand Trust)" as Sarah #E8F5E9
participant "White Buffalo\nEDC Connector" as WB_EDC #E3F2FD
participant "Governance\nKeycloak" as KC #F3E5F5
participant "Caney Fork\nEDC Connector" as CF_EDC #E8F5E9
actor "Will Thompson\n(Caney Fork)" as Will #E8F5E9

== Setup: Caney Fork publishes benchmarking offer ==

Will -> CF_EDC : Publishes grazing rotation data\nwith **members-only** access policy\nand **benchmarking-terms** contract policy
note right of CF_EDC
  Access: Any active GLCDI member
  Contract:
  - Purpose: benchmarking or internal analysis
  - Time limit: 2026-09-30
  - Attribution required
  - No redistribution
  - No commercial use
end note

== Sarah discovers and negotiates ==

Sarah -> WB_EDC : Logs in (via governance Keycloak)
note right of KC
  Sarah's token claims:
  **glcdi_membership**: "active"
  **glcdi_participant_type**: "producer"
  **glcdi_certification_status**: "regenerative-verified"
end note

Sarah -> WB_EDC : Browse Caney Fork catalog
WB_EDC -> CF_EDC : DSP Catalog Query

group Access Policy: members-only
  CF_EDC -> CF_EDC : glcdi_membership == "active" ? **YES**
  note right of CF_EDC
    Sarah is an active member.
    Grazing rotation data is **visible**.
  end note
end

CF_EDC --> WB_EDC : Catalog with grazing rotation offer
WB_EDC --> Sarah : Shows offer with benchmarking terms

Sarah -> WB_EDC : Accepts terms\npurpose = "RegionalBenchmarking"
WB_EDC -> CF_EDC : Contract negotiation

group Contract Policy: benchmarking-terms
  CF_EDC -> CF_EDC : purpose in ["RegionalBenchmarking",\n"InternalAnalysis"] ? **YES**
  CF_EDC -> CF_EDC : dateTime <= 2026-09-30 ? **YES**
  note right of CF_EDC
    => **AGREED**
  end note
end

CF_EDC --> WB_EDC : Contract FINALIZED

== Data Transfer ==

Sarah -> WB_EDC : Request transfer
WB_EDC -> CF_EDC : DSP Transfer
CF_EDC --> WB_EDC : Grazing rotation dataset\n(AMP rotation, stocking density, rest periods)

== Sarah uses the data ==

hnote over Sarah #E8F5E9
  Sarah compares Caney Fork's
  rotation schedule against
  White Buffalo's own practices.

  She can see:
  - Stocking density differences
  - Rest period durations
  - Seasonal rotation patterns

  She discovers that Caney Fork
  uses longer rest periods (45 vs
  her 30 days), correlating with
  higher SOC gains.
end hnote

note over Sarah
  **What Sarah CAN do:**
  - Compare against her own data internally
  - Discuss anonymised insights at
    GLCDI Dataspace Authority meetings
  - Adjust her own practices based
    on what she learns

  **What Sarah CANNOT do:**
  - Share Caney Fork's raw data
    with her funders or partners
  - Use the data in a paid
    consulting report
  - Forward to non-GLCDI participants
end note

== Reciprocal sharing ==

Sarah -> WB_EDC : Publishes her own grazing data\nwith same policy terms
note over WB_EDC
  White Buffalo reciprocates by publishing
  their data under the same benchmarking
  terms. This builds the peer comparison
  dataset that benefits all participants.
end note

Will -> CF_EDC : Discovers White Buffalo's offer
Will -> CF_EDC : Negotiates & transfers
note over Will
  Both ranchers now have each other's
  grazing data for comparison.
  The benchmarking service can
  aggregate both into regional insights.
end note

@enduml
